.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-SCB-BACKUP" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-scb-backup \- export a static channel backup (SCB)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-scb-backup
.RI [ output_path ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Calls
.B lightning-cli staticbackup
and writes the binary SCB to
.I output_path
(default
.IR ./static_channel_backup_<timestamp>.bin ).
Returns
.B {"ok":true}
with the path and byte count on success.
Returns an error object if the daemon is unreachable or no SCB is available.
.PP
Output:
.nf
{"ok":true,"path":...,"size":N}
{"ok":false,"reason":...}
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-wallet-backup (1),
.BR lightning-scb (1)
